## 6. Verify

```bash
cd /path/to/repo
echo "test" >> README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "test: claude-bot identity check"
git push
```

On GitHub, open the commit. The author should show as `claude-bot[bot]` with the
bot badge, linked to your App's bot account — not to you.

If the author shows as a plain string with no badge, the email format is wrong.
Double-check `<APP_ID>+<SLUG>[bot]@users.noreply.github.com` exactly.

If push fails with 403, check:

- The App is installed on this specific repo (§2).
- The App has Contents: Read & write.
- The remote is HTTPS, not SSH.
- `~/.config/claude-github-app/get-token.sh` returns a token without error.

