## 8. Secret boundary: what ships in the mirror vs. what stays local

This repo is published to a **read-only public mirror** and pulled down as
`~/.claude`. Be deliberate about which artifacts cross that boundary:

| Artifact | Home | In the mirror? |
|---|---|---|
| `gh_wrapper` | `~/.claude/bin/gh_wrapper` (from `bin/` in this repo) | **Yes** — generic, no secrets |
| Hook deny rule | `hooks/auto-approve-compound-commands.sh` | **Yes** — logic only |
| `get-token.sh`, `credential-helper.sh`, `init-repo.sh` | `~/.config/claude-github-app/` | **No** — kept with the key by cohesion |
| `config` (`APP_ID`, `INSTALLATION_ID`, `BOT_*`) | `~/.config/claude-github-app/config` | **No** — identifies your App/install |
| `private-key.pem` | `~/.config/claude-github-app/private-key.pem` | **No — never.** Full App impersonation |
| `.token-cache` | `~/.config/claude-github-app/.token-cache` | **No — never.** Holds a live ≤1h token |

The three helper scripts contain no secret text, but they live in the
un-mirrored `~/.config/claude-github-app/` **by cohesion**: keeping the key and
the only code that reads it in one non-mirrored directory means no `.gitignore`
slip can ever leak the PEM through the public repo. Set them up per-machine (a
separate, non-mirrored bootstrap), not via this repo.

`gh_wrapper` is the exception that *is* mirrored: it references the token script
only by absolute path and contains nothing App-specific, so it's safe everywhere
and degrades to plain `gh` when the App isn't present.

