## 9. Rotation & hygiene

- **Installation tokens** rotate themselves every hour; the cache script handles
  this.
- **Private key**: rotate from the App settings page periodically. Generate a
  new key, replace the PEM, delete the old key from GitHub. Then `rm
  ~/.config/claude-github-app/.token-cache` — rotating the PEM stops you minting
  *new* tokens with the old key, but any token already in the cache stays valid
  until its own ≤1h expiry. Deleting the cache forces an immediate fresh mint
  with the new key.
- **Permissions**: review the App's permissions when use cases change. Adding a
  permission requires re-accepting the install on each repo.
- **Audit**: org **Settings → Audit log**, filter `actor:claude-bot[bot]`, to
  see everything the App has done.
- **Revoke fast**: uninstall the App from a repo (or the org) to immediately cut
  off all Claude access without touching your own credentials.

